{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":1,"author":{"id":"e6c152d440109efdc7afc4e9ac4ac193043f8f68"},"timestamp":1397890716,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUzMTgzOTE0OQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/letoram/arcan/issues/70","origin":"github"},"title":"(lua) allow disjoint parallelism","message":"Currently, all calculations in the lua state is done on the rendering thread and due to the tight coupling with the API and the rendering loop things will stay that way.\n\nTo enable multithreaded use in a reasonably safe way, the suggestion is to:\nadd a calc_thread(inptbl, calcfun, callback) function \nwhich will create a new lua_state with only the basic APIs enabled (math, string, ...), a hard memory limit (and GC disabled) with a shallow copy of inptbl. When execution finishes, callback is invoked with a shallow copy of the calcfun return value (or when calcfun issues a yield(value) call).","files":null}]}